# CHIP v2 blackwell-sm-imported
Full Name: NVIDIA Blackwell Streaming Multiprocessor (Imported)
Description:
A textual representation of a streaming multiprocessor assembled from reusable text fragments.
Architecture Goals:
- Express the SM as composable modules
- Reuse shared text fragments through IMPORT
- Keep parsing deterministic and auditable
Modules:
IMPORT fragments/warp-scheduler.chipfrag
IMPORT fragments/tensor-core.chipfrag
Define module Register File:
Summary: Stores per-thread register state.
Operations: read, write, allocate
Inputs: thread id, register index, write value
Outputs: register value, allocation status
Instantiate:
Create 4 instances of Warp Scheduler
Create 8 instances of Tensor Core
Create 1 instances of Register File
Connect:
Warp Scheduler -> Tensor Core
Tensor Core -> Register File
Output: Imported SM tile with scheduling, tensor execution, and register storage.
